gher burden of motor symptoms.","endpoint_type":"secondary"},{"measure":"CGIC, PGIC, CGI-C:CVR","time_frame":"Baseline to 6 months","description":"Clinician, patient, and caregiver global impressions of change. Each is a single item assessment rated from 1 (very much improved) to 7 (very much worse). A higher score indicates worsening symptoms.","endpoint_type":"secondary"}],"eligibility_criteria":"Inclusion Criteria:\n\n* Patients seen in the neurology clinic at UT Health San Antonio\n* Diagnosed with psychosis due to PD or DLB\n* Requiring initiation of an antipsychotic medication\n* Clinical equipoise between quetiapine and pimavanserin must exist\n* The prescribing provider must be comfortable prescribing and managing both quetiapine and pimavanserin\n\nExclusion Criteria:\n\n* Medical contraindication to either medication\n* Caregiver unavailable to complete NPI-Q\n* Currently taking an antipsychotic medication\n* Prescribing provider unwilling to manage either medication","minimum_age":null,"maximum_age":null,"sex":"ALL","source_id":"ctgov:NCT05590637"},"asset_identity":{"nct_id":"NCT05590637","asset_name":"Pimavanserin","raw_intervention_names":["Pimavanserin","Quetiapine"],"intervention_type":"DRUG","aliases":["Nuplazid","Oral Capsule","Oral Tablet","Oral Product","Pill","pimavanserin","pimavanserin tartrate","pimavanserin 10 MG Oral Tablet [Nuplazid]","pimavanserin 34 MG Oral Capsule [Nuplazid]","pimavanserin 10 MG [Nuplazid]","pimavanserin 34 MG [Nuplazid]","pimavanserin Oral Tablet [Nuplazid]","pimavanserin Oral Capsule [Nuplazid]","Nuplazid Oral Product","Nuplazid Pill","pimavanserin 10 MG Oral Tablet","pimavanserin 34 MG Oral Capsule","pimavanserin 10 MG","pimavanserin 34 MG","pimavanserin Oral Tablet"],"rxnorm_match":{"matched_name":"Nuplazid","rxcui":"1791685","aliases":["Nuplazid","Oral Capsule","Oral Tablet","Oral Product","Pill","pimavanserin","pimavanserin tartrate","pimavanserin 10 MG Oral Tablet [Nuplazid]","pimavanserin 34 MG Oral Capsule [Nupl